						               													<description>Sovereign is a game similar to Risk, Settlers of Catan, and Monopoly, if all were rolled into one game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players will manage their TEMPER Attributes in order to remain in power. TEMPER stands for Trustworthiness, Economics, Military, Population, Environment, and Resources. Each of these Attributes are needed to maintain a healthy nation and a healthy ruler.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players will spend 1/2 of each Round in a specific phase, played at the same time. Event Phases are set up as follows:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Players draw event cards.&amp;#10;     Players solve event cards in one minute.&amp;#10;     Players vote on other player's solutions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The second phase is the Action Phase, where players expand by buying tiles or trading for them, build Resource collectors, or make armies. There's a lot you can do during this phase.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players will play until either all are eliminated or one Sovereign remains.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
